      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "For example, when a program fails with a \"division by zero\" exception, it does not tell where the zero comes from; a debugger may need to back track the data flow to find the source of the zero. Secondly, treatments of a bug (i.e., changes made to fix the bug) may often contain not only treatments for bugs but also non-essential changes (e.g., code reformatting, code refactoring, etc.) [CITATION_1] , new feature additions, many of which are intermingled."
